          \end{tabular}
 \caption{Snapshot of the Phases of $100$ Oscillators after $80000$ iterations revealing various Collective Dynamical States: (clockwise from top left) (a) Asynchronous State for $\epsilon=0.5, r=0.02$, (b) Multichimera State for $\epsilon=0.5, r=0.35$, (c) Synchronized State for $\epsilon=0.8, r=0.45$ and (d) Chimera State for $\epsilon=0.98, r=0.37$.}
\end{center}
\end{figure}

In our simulation, we have first considered $N=100$ number of oscillators and assumed $l=50$. Depending
on the values of coupling strength ($\epsilon$) and coupling radius ($r$), we
have observed various dynamical modes/states of the oscillators. For small,
values of $\epsilon$ and $r$, the oscillators are seen to oscillate 
incoherently showing an asynchronous dynamical state even after a 
long time ($t=40000$). This is shown in Fig-1(a). 
A typical video may be found
in ref. \cite{video1}. For sufficiently large values of 
$\epsilon$ and $r$, we have found a complete 
synchronous state, when all the oscillators are found to 
oscillate coherently. 
A typical video may be found in ref. \cite{video2}. Fig-1(c)
shows such synchronized state of the oscillators. The most interesting state
was observed in the intermediate range of values of $\epsilon$ and $r$. Here,
for a range of $\epsilon$ and $r$ values, we observed that multiple groups of
connected oscillators oscillate in a synchronized fashion. This is similar to
multichimera states found in previous works\cite{panaggio} and shown in Fig-1(b,d). The dynamical evolution to 
multichimera state can be found in a video in ref. \cite{video3}.

